vulnerability.name: USN-5739-1
vulnerability.description: Several security issues were discovered in MariaDB and this update includes new upstream MariaDB versions to fix these issues.  MariaDB has been updated to 10.3.37 in Ubuntu 20.04 LTS and to 10.6.11 in Ubuntu 22.04 LTS and Ubuntu 22.10.  In addition to security fixes, the updated packages contain bug fixes, new features, and possibly incompatible changes.

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in MariaDB.
